Betr: Entschadigungssache George
Gerard (fr. Bursch) nach dem Vater
Alexander Bursch
Der Regierungsprasident
I E B 227 445 a (51)
State of New York
County of New York
SS
Valeria Gerard, being duly sworn, deposes and says:
1. I make this affidavit at the request of Der Regierungsprasident,
in support of the claim of my son, George Gerard, to obtain resti-
tution of property, assets and damages arising out of the seizure of
such assets from my former husband, Alexander Bursch.
2. My former husband, from whom I was divorced in 1925, was born
on or about August 1, 1880, in Zittau, Saxony. He inherited from his
father, Heinrich, considerable property and assets. These included two
department stores in Zittau which my former husband owned and
managed himself. He also owned several large buildings in Dresden,
Berlin and a villa in Harlachingen, a suburb of Munich. Amongst other
assets, he owned a hotel in Dresden, named,Hotel Stadt Rom,"
which he managed and operated until approximately 1934 or 1935 when
Hitler came to power.
3. My former husband was a very wealthy man and besides his assets
listed above, he also had very substantial deposits in banks located
in the various cities in which his assets were situated.
4. In addition, my former husband was the owner of two very rare
and valuable violins, made by Guarneri, and which were valued even
in those days at a sum in excess of $30,000.00 each.
5. After Hitler came into power, gradually all of my former husband's
property and assets, including everything listed above, was forcibly
taken from him by the Nazis because of the fact that he was Jewish.
6. In or about 1940 I received word from my former sister-in-law,
Adele Goldman, advising me that Alexander Bursch had been killed
while in prison or concentration camp, by the Nazis, where he had
been placed because of his Jewish background. I was also advised
that he had been stripped of all of his fortune and assets. That was the
last word that either I, my son or any other member of the family ever
heard of my former husband,
Valeria Sicard
worn to before me this
lay of April, 1963
Tanen C.
Billy
WARREN C. BRADLEY
stary Public, State of New York
No. 24-5416040
uld in
County
k County Cork
30, 1964
